
Order Management System

A Django-based RESTful application for managing restaurant operations: menu, inventory, tables, reservations, and orders. Designed to streamline restaurant workflow and ensure accurate order and stock management.

Features

CRUD for Menu, Inventory, Tables, Reservations, and Orders
Automatic inventory tracking and stock updates
Table availability checks for reservations and orders
REST API endpoints for integration
Manage all data via Django admin panel

Technology Stack

Python, Django, Django REST Framework
MySQL
Git & GitHub

API Endpoints (examples)

/menu/ – List/Create menu items

/inventory/ – List/Create inventory items

/tables/ – List/Create tables

/reservations/ – List/Create reservations

/orders/ – List/Create orders

Setup
git clone https://github.com/Usman-54/CodeAlpha_Tasks.git
cd CodeAlpha_Tasks
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
python manage.py runserver


Access admin panel: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
and the admin is codeapha and also email and and as well password.
